<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Blood Defiance</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Blood Defiance">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
MAGIC 
LORE 
NO DROP 



<br><br>


<b>Inventory Slots:</b> Primary
<br>

<b>Weapon Type:</b> 1HSlash<br><br>


<b>Damage:</b> 22<br>
<b>Delay:</b> 24<br>
<b>Damage/Second:</b> 18.75<br><br>

<b>Modifiers:</b> Sta +8, HP +35, Mana +50, SV D +12<br>
<b>Size:</b> Medium<br>
<b>Weight:</b> 2.5<br>

<br>
<b>Classes:</b> SHD<br>
<b>Races:</b> ALL<br>


<b>Recommended Level:</b> 53<br>


<br>

















<br><table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Found On 

<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqbestiaryfull&eqbestiary.mob_name=%22Raddi%20Adan%22">Raddi Adan</a></b></font></table><br>
<b>Level:</b> 68 - 68<br>
<b>Classification:</b> Rare_Monster<br>
<b>Sociality:</b> Social<br>









<br><b>Description</b>:<br>- Spawns during Bertoxxulous event.<BR>- Immune to Slow<br>

<br><table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Obtained in 
<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Ring%20of%20Bertoxxulous%22">Ring of Bertoxxulous</a> Quest</b></font></table><br>
<b>Recommended Level:</b> 61<br>
<b>Starting NPC:</b> Spectre of Corruption<br><br>

<b>Description</b>:<br>
This is the event which spawns Bertoxxulous. It is initiated in the lower portion of the Ruins of Lxanvom. To access this area you must first complete the Lower Crypt of Decay Key quest. It may then be accessed by clicking on the throne near the entrance of the zone.<BR><BR>Once you are in the lower crypt you will notice that there is only one mob here: The Spectre of Corruption. You kill the spectre to initiate the event.<BR><BR>Once the event has begun you some new untargetable mobs will spawn. These mobs will summon the additional adds. You have 2 hours from when the Spectre of Corruption dies in which to kill Bertoxxulous. During that time you must clear the waves of mobs and the twelve kings. It is helpful to pull the mobs as they spawn, but it is normal to fall somewhat behind. The kings reset to their spawn point quicker than the regular mobs, so you can isolate them even if you fall behind using two feign death pullers.<BR><BR>The first wave of kings will come quickly one after another. You must pull the kings, do not worry about them camp rushing you. They spawn at the four different spawner points. The first will spawn when approximately 50 mobs are killed downstairs. The next will each spawn when a few mobs are killed. After the first wave of kings is downed you have another long stretch of mob killing(30 mobs or so) until the second wave spawns. They will again spawn every few mobs for this wave of four. <BR><BR>When the last king in the second wave (eighth overall) dies then the final four kings will spawn. When these are killed Bertoxxulous will spawn in the center room. For this reason it is recommended that you fight the final king on his spawn location instead of pulling him. Fighting in the center room/zone out is a bad idea for the final king.<BR><BR>The flag that you receive from kiling Bertoxxulous is an extension of the Tortured by Nightmares quest which is required for access to the Elemental Planes.<br>


<br><table width="300" bgcolor="#004b97"><b><font color=#d2d200>Found in <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqzone&eqzones.zone_name=%22Ruins%20of%20Lxanvom%22">Ruins of Lxanvom</a></b></font></table><br>
<b>Continent:</b> Planes of Power<br>
<b>Zone Type:</b> Plane<br>
<b>Level Ranges:</b> 55 - 65<br>
<b>Connects To:</b> Plane of Tranquility<br><br>

<b>Description:</b><br>This is a second tier plane after the Plane of Disease. It is also known as the Crypt of Decay. Those who are allowed passage can enter it by clicking on the statue at +1930, -1115 in the Plane of Tranquility. This is in the tunnel that leads downwards near the entrance to the Plane of Disease.<BR><BR>The Ruins of Lxanvom is an indoor plane so I hope you invested some AA points in to increasing your run speed. To exit this zone click on the boulder near the entrance.<BR><BR>Large guilds may gain access to this zone by completing <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Ruins%20of%20Lxanvom%20Entry%22">this quest</a>. Single groups or solo players can gain access through <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Grimror%27s%20Big%20Plans%22">the single group quest</a> instead.<BR><BR>The Ruins of Lxanvom is split up in to two zones. You may access the lower portion of the zone by clicking the Throne near the entrance, if you have the key. You can obtain the key by <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Lower%20Crypt%20of%20Decay%20Key%22">doing this quest</a>.<BR><BR>Once on the lower level you can initiate the <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqquestfull&eqquests.quest_name=%22Ring%20of%20Bertoxxulous%22">Ring of Bertoxxulous</a> event. After killing Bertoxxulous you need to hail the Planar Projection and then return to speak to the Adlar Fuirstell and Elder Fuirstell to further flag yoruself.<BR><BR>It should be noted that those who do the single player quest can not receive this flag, unless they have also completed the large guild quest.<br>




